I ran a [coverage](http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/All/job/gazebo-any-coverage-trusty-amd64/253/) build for this branch last night.

I noticed that the newly introduced functions have only about [28%](http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/All/job/gazebo-any-coverage-trusty-amd64/253/clover-report/_var_lib_jenkins_workspace_gazebo-any-coverage-trusty-amd64_gazebo_gazebo_physics_ode/ODEFixedJoint_cc.html) function coverage, which sort of makes sense since most functions are meaningless for fixed joints. My question is, do we care about the coverage here (we're trying to [improve](http://gazebosim.org/tutorials?tut=contrib_code&cat=development#Testcoverage) the coverage on all new pull requests)? Should there be tests calling these functions at least to make sure they don't break anything? I think that would be quick to implement...
